race.comment: Keen to be with TENTYRIS (2) here. A G2 winner as a 2yo, he was off an injury enforced layoff leading into his fresh run in the G2 Danehill Stakes and the market was keen to oppose him, drifting out to $7.50. Despite that, his run was very good. The outside runners dominated straight racing all day and he was only beaten 1.5 lengths, the first to finish of the inside division. Fitter now and suited around a bend, he'll sit just off them and let rip late. MCGAW (1) won the Danehill as the widest runner as a $15 chance, running relatively slick overall time in the process. He'll land in a good spot here and can repeat the dose. RAGING FORCE (3) comes down from Sydney. His winning streak came to an end in the G2 Run To The Rose, a fast 1200m against the likes of Tempted and Beiwacht seeing him out. If he gets an easy time on speed he'll be very hard to catch. RIPLEY (6) was an easy maiden winner fresh and can run well, ALEPPO PINE (4) perhaps next best although the trip is a query.
